Run leapfrog model fit for a single year

Source: R/run_model.R
run_model_single_year.Rd

Run leapfrog model fit for a single year

run_model_single_year(
  parameters,
  configuration,
  initial_state,
  start_from_year
)

Arguments

parameters

Projection parameters

configuration

The model configuration to run, see list_model_configurations() for available configurations

initial_state

The model will run from this initial state

start_from_year

Start the model simulation from this year

Value

List of model outputs without the last time dimension. This is different from run_model_from_state() and run_model() that do include the last time dimension. Since only the next time step is returned, dropping the time dimensions makes it easier to feed the returned list into the next single year model run. In contrast to run_model_from_state() the p_total_pop output will have dimensions 81 x 2 not 81 x 2 x 61.
